<br>
First... Here's screenshot for you to look at:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://br.crashed.net/~ink/files/NiceModScreenshot.jpg">Screen Shot of the modifications</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
This is what has changed from the original interface:<br>
<br>
Buff window:<br>
      Smaller icons for buffs<br>
      Text description for all buffs (modified since screenshot now has white text for the description)<br>
      15 slot maximum enforced (with text number)<br>
<br>
Player Window (health fatigue mana window):<br>
      Numerical CurrentHP / MaxHP<br>
      Numerical AC<br>
      Health Bar with Percentage<br>
      Mana Bar with Percentage<br>
      Extra thin Fatigue bar<br>
      EXP Bar with Percentage<br>
      AA EXP Bar with percentage<br>
<br>
Target Window:<br>
      Health Bar with Percentage<br>
<br>
Group Window:<br>
      Health Bar with Pecentage for all group members.<br>
<br>
Compass:<br>
      New graphic for compass with dark background, larger white direction letters, and color coded direction tickers.<br>
<br>
All of these mods have been coded to work with the new interface changes since the patch. Here is a link for you to download them:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://br.crashed.net/~ink/files/NiceMods.zip">Get Thangor's Mods Now!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
To install them you need to do the following:<br>
<br>
Go to your folder:<br>
C: \Program Files\Sony\EverQuest Trilogy\uifiles\default<br>
<br>
Next make a copy of all these files in another folder such as:<br>
C: \Program Files\Sony\EverQuest Trilogy\uifiles\thangor<br>
<br>
Next unzip NiceMods.zip (the file you downloaded) into the new folder. Choose to overwrite any files.<br>
<br>
Next load up EQ. When you're in the game type the following:<br>
/loadskin thangor<br>
<br>
**NOTE: make sure you type /loadskin with the foldername you made. I used &quot;thangor&quot; because it's what is in my example.**<br>
<br>
and you're all done! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Enjoy the mods. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
There will be more to come. I will post them in this thread when I work on them.<br>
<br>
